This development has resulted in the dramatic progression in the registration practices and procedures in Bahrain. It is important to note that President of the Bahrain Economic Development Board, he has also formed a specialized committee for the protection of IPIs. This committee’s primary concern is to set up appropriate guidelines and increase knowledge regarding the registration and protection of IP in Bahrain.
The high number of national and international registrations, as well as successful decisions taken by the Appeal Board at Chairman level has laid down a good foundation for Bahrain to be recognized as one of the leading cancellation registrars in the region.
Another accomplishment that Bahrain has achieved is its growth from one user of Trademark and Design Electronic System to three and the imminent fourth. More than a decade ago, the IPO was one of the first offices to adopt this system. Today IPTSystem is being used by our users to do their renewals and recordation of assignments online while CID-back Office allows the IPO to handle office actions efficiently.
Following on the heels of Bahrain’s success in trademark protection came an improved territorial scope, in which three territories in the UAE were now under the umbrella of anti-counterfeiting protection, thereby widening the protection area. This new development enhances Bahrain’s capabilities to effectively counter the unlicensed IP and counterfeiting problems that are rampant in the UAE markets.
